{"parse":{"title":"paddy","pageid":76388,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Paddy}}\n==English==\n{{was wotd|2006|December|16}}\n[[Image:Rice Field.jpg|thumb|right|A rice paddy in Bengal.]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpædi/}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-paddy.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|en-au-paddy.ogg|a=AU}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ædi|s=2}}\n* {{homophone|en|Paddy}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{bor+|en|ms|padi|t=paddy plant}}.  {{doublet|en|palay}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{l|en|rough|Rough}} or [[unhusked]] [[rice]], either before it is [[mill]]ed or as a [[crop]] to be [[harvest]]ed. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2011|author=w:Arupa Patangia Kalita|translator=Deepika Phukan|title=The Story of Felanee\n|passage=Taking out a handful of '''paddy''' the old woman exclaimed, “Look how good this '''paddy''' is! It is called Malbhog – it makes excellent puffed rice.”}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[paddy field]], a [[rice paddy]]; an [[irrigate]]d or [[flood]]ed [[field]] where [[rice]] is [[grown]]. {{defdate|from 20th c.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|paddyland|paddymelon|paddy bird|paddy hat|rice paddy herb}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|rice unmilled}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|ধান}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|ধান}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{t|bcl|pasi}}, {{t+|bcl|tipasi}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|арпа|f}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|စပါး}}, {{t+|my|ကောက်}}\n* Cebuano: {{t|ceb|pasi}}, {{t|ceb|tipasi}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|稻|tr=dào}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[kuorimaton]] [[riisi]]}}, {{t+|fi|paddy}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|paddy|m}}, {{t|fr|riz paddy|m}}\n* Gujarati: {{t+|gu|ધાન}} {{t|gu|સાળ}} {{t+|gu|ડાંગર}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|धान}}\n* Ilocano: {{t|ilo|pagay}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|padi}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|risone|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|稲|tr=ine}}\n* Javanese: {{t+|jv|pari}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|pale}}\n* Karen:\n*: S'gaw Karen: {{t|ksw|ဘု}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|шалы}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|벼}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|padi}}\n* Malayalam: {{t+|ml|നെല്ല്}}\n* Polish: {{t|pl|[[ryż]] [[łuskać|niełuskany]]|m}}\n* Punjabi: {{t|pa|ਝੋਨਾ|m}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|ри́с-па́дди|m}}, {{t|ru|[[необру́шенный]] [[ри́с]]|m}}, {{t|ru|ри́с-сыре́ц|m}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t+|si|කුඹුර}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|arroz con cáscara|m}}, {{t|es|arroz en cáscara|m}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|palay}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|వడ్లు}}, {{t|te|అరికెలు}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|ข้าวเปลือก}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|çeltik}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|چلتیك|tr=çeltik}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|reis cibynnog|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n{{trans-top|wet land where rice grows}}\n* Acehnese: {{t|ace|blang}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t|af|rys veld}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|orizore|m}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|حَقْل اَلْأَرُزّ|m}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|ধাননি}}\n* Banjarese: {{t+|bjn|pahumaan}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|рысавыя палі|m}}\n* Bengali: {{t|bn|ধানজমি|tr=dhanjômi}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{t+|bcl|kabasan}}, {{t|bcl|paruyan}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|оризище|m}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|လယ်}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|arrossar|m}}\n* Cebuano: {{t|ceb|humayan}}, {{t|ceb|kahumayan}}, {{t|ceb|pilapil}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|稻田|tr=dou6 tin4}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|稻田|tr=dàotián}}, {{t+|cmn|水田|tr=shuǐtián}}\n* Czech: {{t|cs|rýžové pole|m}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|rismark|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|rijstveld|n}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|rizejo}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|riisipõld}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|riisipelto}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|rizière|f}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|arrozal|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Reisfeld|n}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ορυζώνας|m}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|loʻi}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|שדה אורז|m}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|धान का क्षेत्र|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|rizsföld}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|hrísgrjónaakur|m}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|sawah}}, {{t|id|sawah padi}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|riissupelto}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|risaia|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|田|tr=[[た]], ta}}, {{t+|ja|水田|tr=[[すいでん]], suiden}}, {{t+|ja|田んぼ|tr=tanbo}}\n* Javanese: {{t+|jv|sawah}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|ស្រែ|tr=srae}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|논}}, {{t+|ko|답(畓)}},  {{t+|ko|수전(水田)}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ນາ}}, {{t|lo|ນາເຂົ້າ}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|lietinimas|m}}\n* Lü: {{t|khb|ᦓᦱ}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|оризово поле|m}}\n* Malagasy: {{t+|mg|akotry}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|sawah}}, {{t|ms|sawah padi}}\n* Malayalam: {{t|ml|നെല്പാടം}}, {{t+|ml|പാടം}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|māra}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|no|rismark|m}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|شالیزار|tr=šâlizâr}}, {{t+|fa|گرنجار|tr=gorenjâr}}, {{t+|fa|برنجار|tr=berenjâr}}\n* Polish: {{t|pl|[[pole]] [[ryżowy|ryżowe]]|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|arrozal|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|orezărie|f}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|[[рисовый|ри́совое]] [[по́ле]]|n}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|рижино поље|m}}, {{t|sh|пиринчано поље|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|rižino polje|m}}, {{t|sh|pirinčano polje|m}}\n* Shan: {{t+|shn|ၼႃး}}\n* Sikkimese: {{t|sip|ཆུ་ཞིང}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|arrozal|m}}\n* Sundanese: {{t+|su|sawah}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|risfält|n}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|palayan}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|நெல் வயல்}}\n* Tày: {{t|tyz|nà}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|นา}}, {{t|th|นาข้าว}}\n*: Northern Thai: {{t|nod|ᨶᩣ}}\n* Tulu: {{t+|tcy|ಬೆನ್ನಿ}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|pirinç tarlası}}, {{t+|tr|çeltik tarlası}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|چلتیك|tr=çeltik}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|[[ruộng]] [[lúa]]}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|risataläned}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|cae reis|m}}\n* Zhuang: {{t|za|naz}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nEnglish dialect {{m|en|paddy||worm-eaten}}.\n\n====Adjective====\n{{en-adj}}\n\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} Low; mean; boorish; vagabond.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1860|author=w:John Lothrop Motley|title=The United Netherlands\n|passage=Even after the expiration of four months the condition of the '''paddy''' persons continued most destitute. The English soldiers became mere barefoot starving beggars in the streets{{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1995| title=D.S. MacColl: Painter, Poet, Art Critic |author=Maureen Borland | page=41| passage=Becca wrote to Lizzie of her brother's incessant demands: ''Suthie came to me in a very '''paddy''' state and said 'Now ... you must bind a book for me.' ''}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2015| title=An Evil Cradling|author=Brian Keenan|page=197|passage=Now, now, we are getting very '''paddy''' today, aren't we John?}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\nPossibly from {{m|en|Paddy|t=Irishman}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A fit of [[temper]]; a [[tantrum]].\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:tantrum}}\n#: {{ux|en|throw a '''paddy''''' etc.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2013|author=w:Mike Brown|title=Adventures with Czech George|page=17|passage=I like the story of the Emperor Frederick who got into a '''paddy''' with his cook, and shouted: 'I am the Emperor, and I want dumplings.'}}\n# {{lb|en|AAVE|slang}} A [[white]] person.\n#* {{quote-av|en|year=2000|actor=Keith David|role=Big Tim\n|title=Requiem For a Dream|text=You know what I like best about '''paddy''' chicks? They give good head. Black broads don’t know nothing about giving head. I don’t know why. Might be it has something to do with some ancient tribal custom.}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial|England}} A [[labourer]]'s [[assistant]] or [[workmate]].\n# A [[drill]] used in boring wells, with cutters that expand on pressure.\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|kri|pàdí}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 4===\nPerhaps after the [[paddy bird]], or [[egret]]. {{rfe|en}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A [[snowy sheathbill]].\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|paddy paw}}\n\n{{C|en|Agriculture|Anger|People|Tools}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|fr|en|paddy}}, from {{der|fr|ms|padi}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Bananax47-paddy.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Agen>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|paddy}} {{gl|rice}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n{{C|fr|Agriculture}}"}}